Simple command line client for http://beanstalkapp.com.

Right now the only thing it can do is to create repositories.

Preparation:

Install beanstalkapp gem.

Then add your Beanstalk API settings into your ~/.beanstalkrc file in following format:

  domain: "your-account"
  login: "your-login"
  password: "your-password"

Make sure you have API access enabled in Beanstalk's account settings.

Usage:

  $ jacky repository create my-repo git "My New Repository"
